<div class="callout warn">
  <div class="callout-title">Trial-aware: three pedagogical arms</div>
  <p>Unit 5 is Matthew's trial unit. Three sections, three slightly different scaffolds, same skill being built:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Section A (BoodleBox arm)</strong>: students <em>build</em> their own Stakeholder Voice AI bot for their chosen stakeholder — the <strong>Boodle Build Assignment</strong>. The 8-section system-prompt template guides identity + beliefs + strongest argument + non-negotiable + honest admission + opponent-framing + cited evidence + constraints. Peer-tested in Block 8. AI Doc covers the build process explicitly.</li>
    <li><strong>Section B (Flint guided-tutor arm)</strong>: students work with pre-built Flint Stakeholder Voice tutors. Mr. Ignash configures the stakeholder personas; students push for the strongest version of the position. Linear scaffolding, consistent voice across stakeholders.</li>
    <li><strong>Section C (paper-based arm)</strong>: students work from paper-based Stakeholder Profile Packs (7 detailed Q&amp;A profiles per case, no AI). Same skill via close reading + interview-style preparation.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Each scaffold is designed to teach the same perspective-taking skill — pedagogically distinct, not quality-ranked. Your section's tools are introduced on Day 1.</p>
</div>

